      <hedline>
        <hl1>Violin Lesson's Test</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Michael Symons letter on Isaac Stern's violin lesson for New York City school superintendents; says true test will come when they confront next budget crisis (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''43 Superintendents Do Their Best Jack Benny'' (news article, May 11):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''43 Superintendents Do Their Best Jack Benny'' (news article, May 11):</p>
        <p>The true test of Isaac Stern's violin lesson for the New York City school superintendents will come when they are confronted with the next budget crisis. If the money is lacking, will they put the arts last?</p>
        <p>MICHAEL SYMONS  Brooklyn, May 12, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
